A Malindi court has ordered a psychiatric examination of one of the six men charged with defrauding a family of two parcels of land worth Sh700 million. Malindi chief magistrate Dr Julie Oseko directed Hassan Juma to be taken to Port Reiz hospital after his lawyer raised concern about his mental status. Juma is among six elderly men who were slapped with Sh20 million bond with two sureties of a similar amount each. All of them failed to raise the bond and have been at the Malindi GK Prison remand for two weeks. Those facing charges include Ramadhan Ramadhan, Abubakar Kombo, Musa Juma, Juma r Korshen, Juma Juma and Saburi Shebani .    